Target: OntoLab is an ontology developed for expressing facilities in a research lab.

Comment: Facility that provides controlled conditions in which scientific or technological research, experiments, and measurement may be performed. [https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q483242]
Equipment used for laboratory experiments. [https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q834028]
Specifications that are used to set the operating conditions of laboratory equipment.
Each parameter setting refers to one specific setting of the laboratory equipment.
Setting that specifies the temperature.
Setting that specifies the duration.
Setting that specifies the flow rate.
Setting that specifies the volume.
Power supply of lab equipment.
External power supply through DC.
Power supply through a lithium battery.
Power supply through an external battery.
Power supply through a NiMH rechargeable battery.
Power supply through a solar power pack.
The concrete realisation of chemical amount in the physical world, e.g., a liquid holdup in a vessel.
Preparation method of a chemical amount.
The chemical amount is repurified from received.
The chemical amount is dried from received.
The chemical amount is sparged from received.
The chemical amount is used as received.
The chemical amount is synthesised in house.
A container in the lab that is filled with chemical amount.
The container that hosts chemical stock solutions.
The container that hosts waste chemicals.
The container that hosts a small amount of chemical amount.
The relationship between lab equipment and the agent service that manages it.
The relation between the laboratory and the lab equipment located in it.
The relation specifies the price of a laboratory equipment.
The relation specifies the weight of a laboratory equipment.
The relation specifies the height of a laboratory equipment.
The relation specifies the width of a laboratory equipment.
The relation specifies the length of a laboratory equipment.
The relation specifies the power supply type of a laboratory equipment.
The relation between the chemical amount and its preparation method.
The relation between the chemical container and the chemical amount it contains.
The relation indicates the fill level of a chemical container below which a warning to researcher should be sent.
The relation indicates the current filling level of a chemical container.
The relation indicates the maximum filling level of a chemical container.
The relation between the equipment settings and the laboratory equipment it governs.
The relation between the equipment settings and the reaction experiment it was generated for.
The relation between the equipment settings and its individual parameter setting.
The relation between the parameter setting and the quantity it refers to following the units of measure practice.
The timestamp when the state of lab equipment was last updated at.
The boolean flag to indicate if there are unidentified components in the collected chemical amount.
